      "article": "210.8(F)",
      "summary": "Amended outdoor outlet GFCI threshold from 50 amperes to 20 amperes. For dwellings, all outdoor outlets supplied by 125-volt single-phase branch circuits rated 150 volts or less to ground, 20 amperes or less, shall be provided with GFCI protection, including outlets in: (1) Garages at or below grade, (2) Accessory buildings, (3) Boathouses. If equipment supplied by a covered outlet is replaced, the outlet shall be provided with GFCI protection. Exception No. 1: GFCI not required on lighting outlets other than those covered in 210.8(C). Exception No. 2: GFCI not required for listed HVAC equipment. This exception expires September 1, 2026."
    },
    {
      "article": "210.12",
      "summary": "Restructured AFCI requirements. New section (C) added - Dormitory Units: All 120-volt, single-phase, 10-, 15-, and 20-ampere branch circuits supplying outlets or devices in dormitory units shall be AFCI protected in: (1) through (4) unchanged, (5) Bathrooms. New section (D) added - Other Occupancies: All 120-volt, single-phase, 10-, 15-, and 20-ampere branch circuits supplying outlets or devices in the following locations shall be AFCI protected: (1) Guest rooms and guest suites of hotels and motels, (2) Areas used exclusively as patient sleeping rooms in nursing homes and limited-care facilities, (3) Areas designed for use exclusively as sleeping quarters in fire stations, police stations, ambulance stations, rescue stations, ranger stations, and similar locations. Section (E) - Branch Circuit Wiring Extensions, Modifications, or Replacements: Applies to areas specified in 210.12(B), (C), or (D)."
