      "article": "314.27(C)",
      "summary": "Outlet boxes in habitable rooms of dwelling occupancies at ceiling locations acceptable for a ceiling-suspended (paddle) fan shall comply with one of the following: (1) Listed for sole support of ceiling-suspended fans, or (2) An outlet box complying with 314.27 and providing access to structural framing capable of supporting a fan bracket. Where spare, separately switched, ungrounded conductors are provided to a ceiling outlet box in a location acceptable for a fan in one-family, two-family, or multifamily dwellings, the outlet box shall be listed for sole support of a ceiling-suspended fan. Boxes shall not support fans exceeding 70 lb; boxes supporting fans over 35 lb shall be marked with maximum weight."
