      "summary": "AC disconnect location requirements amended. Disconnecting means shall be within sight from and readily accessible from the equipment. May be installed on or within the equipment. Shall not be located on access panels that obscure nameplate(s). Exception No. 1: Industrial process refrigerating or AC equipment where disconnect is lockable per 110.25, with written safety procedures and only qualified persons service. Exception No. 2: Attachment plug and receptacle serving as disconnect per 440.13 shall be accessible but not required to be readily accessible. Exception No. 3: Disconnect for indoor unit of a ductless mini-split system not required if the outdoor condensing unit disconnect is lockable in the open position per 110.25."
